# claude-daily-digest — per-install configuration.
# Generated by setup.sh. You can edit this by hand at any time.

# Email address where the daily digest is sent. Must match the Gmail/Workspace
# account that issued the app password stored in System keychain.
EMAIL="you@example.com"

# A paragraph describing your role, stack, workflows, and constraints.
# This gets injected into the prompt so the digest can personalize its
# "why it matters" and "features worth trying" sections.
#
# Good paragraphs answer five questions:
#   1. Who are you and what do you build?     (role, company, stack)
#   2. How do you use Claude Code?            (skills, MCPs, workflows)
#   3. What have you already adopted?         (don't re-recommend)
#   4. What are your constraints?             (plan tier, hardware, etc.)
#   5. What do you care most about?           (cost, speed, reliability, novelty)
#
# Also tell the daemon what NOT to bother you with (Bedrock/Vertex/Windows
# if those don't apply).
#
# The daemon also reads your ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md, rules, installed skills,
# Context OS index, and project folder names automatically — so don't
# repeat that list here. Focus on priorities and preferences the files
# can't reveal.
#
# If you want more control than this paragraph gives, edit templates/prompt.tpl
# directly — USER_WORKFLOWS is only one substitution; the whole prompt is yours.
USER_WORKFLOWS="General software development. No specific framework preferences. Interested in MCP reliability, model updates, and cost-saving features."

# Absolute path to this installation. Used by daily-review.sh to locate the
# prompt template, digests, emails, and logs. Set by setup.sh.
INSTALL_DIR="$HOME/claude-daily-digest"

# launchd label / msmtp keychain service name. Setup.sh derives these from
# your username so multiple users on one Mac don't collide. You usually
# don't need to change these.
LAUNCHD_LABEL="com.youruser.claude-daily-digest"
KEYCHAIN_SERVICE="msmtp-claude-daily-digest"

# Absolute path to the `claude` CLI. Setup.sh auto-detects this. If you
# move your Homebrew prefix or install the CLI elsewhere, update here.
CLAUDE_BIN="/opt/homebrew/bin/claude"

# Model + effort passed to `claude -p`. Change if you want cheaper runs.
# See: https://docs.claude.com/en/docs/claude-code/cli-reference
CLAUDE_MODEL="claude-opus-4-7"
CLAUDE_EFFORT="xhigh"
